content: The primary library is a local library of a more popular community nature. It is large in scale and has perfect infrastructure. The local people like it better. There are bicycle sheds nearby. It has a special atmosphere of life.

The Primary Reading Library is located at the former site of the University of Gyeonggi in Beicun, Zhonglu District, Seoul. It opened in January 1977 and has a collection of 490,000 books and 16,300 non-book materials. The Seoul Education Archive contains 12,000 Uge Education materials, which is the Seoul Municipal Public Library. The Reading Library provides recent intelligence to Seoul citizens and is committed to helping them learn, achieve cultural development and lifelong education. In addition to borrowing books and materials, writers are invited to lecture every month, and there are also frequent photography exhibitions, reading clubs, puppet dramas, concerts, dance performances and other rich cultural activities.

The Mengcun History Museum occupies a small area. There is a dynamic interactive round sand plate of the Mengcun Tucheng Cultural Relics Group in the middle of the hall. After bypassing the round sand plate, the left hand side is in turn the Fengna Tucheng Cultural Relics Area, the Ancient Life Cultural Relics Area, the brick and tiles of the Three Kingdoms Period, the cultural relics experience platform, Seoul's Koguryo culture and Seoul's Silla culture are opposite the Baiji later cultural exhibition area and the ancient East Asian cultural exchange exhibition area, and will eventually return to the door.

The Prison History Memorial Hall is a monument to Korean history that historically records the past 100 years of Korean history - which is why visitors to Seoul must go to that place. By visiting it, everyone can understand part of South Korea's history and the incredible power of the Korean people to stand up for themselves.
